Does it makes sense to have a function — `targs` that transforms an argument object to a key value pair?

``` javascript

const targs = function () {
  const toArr = x => [].slice.call(x)
  const keys = toArr(arguments)
  return function () {
    const out = {}
    const values = toArr(arguments)
    values.forEach((x, i) => out[keys[i]] = x)
    return out
  }
}

```

Here are some useful examples —
### Example 1 — Create a key value pair from an object

``` javascript
_.map({a: 1, b: 2, c: 3}, targs('value', 'key')) 

/* OUTPUTS
  [
    {key: 'a', value: 1},
    {key: 'b', value: 2},
    {key: 'c', value: 3}
  ]
*/
```
